# crawl-logs allowlist — one regex per line.
# Lines starting with '#' are comments. Matched WARN/ERROR signatures
# are excluded from the per-signature repeat-count threshold so we
# don't fail CI on benign first-time-only operator notices.
#
# Add an entry only with a one-line rationale comment above it.

# SQLite EXPERIMENTAL operator notice (warn-once latch enforces single emission per process,
# but parallel vitest workers each emit once → can exceed maxRepeat with no actual bug).
EXPERIMENTAL: SQLite (storage )?backend

# Prompt review service operates with an optional config file; absence is expected
# in CI and unit tests. Logged at WARN with stack but is a benign operational miss.
\[promptReviewService\] WARN: Could not locate PROMPT-CRITERIA\.json

# Embedding store rebuild on corruption is a self-healing path tests intentionally
# trigger via "file is not a database" fixtures. Counted but not a regression signal.
\[embedding-store\] (Integrity check error|Rebuilding corrupt database|Search query dimension mismatch)

# Test fixtures inject deliberate registry tool errors to exercise error paths.
\[registry\] Tool error: (messaging_|feedback_)

# Negative tests feed the index loader intentionally bad generated test-N files
# to verify schema rejection. Counted but expected.
\[index:skip\] test-\d+\.json: schema: /sourceHash:

# Other index loader negative fixtures intentionally feed malformed instruction
# files to verify skip/error reporting.
\[index:skip\]

# Auto-migration failure path test fixture. The fix-loop-guard ensures it fires once
# per process; the test triggers it deliberately. Real regressions would repeat per request.
\[storage\] Auto-migration failed:

# CI workflow plants a minimal ci-seed.json that intentionally doesn't match the full
# instruction schema (it's a placeholder so instructions/ is non-empty for the loader test).
\[index:skip\] ci-seed\.json:

# Node.js process-level warnings (MaxListenersExceededWarning, ExperimentalWarning, etc.)
# are logged by the indexServer adapter; tests deliberately exercise high-fanout paths.
\[indexServer\] Process warning

# Input-validation surface: search service logs invalid keyword/regex/limit attempts at
# WARN with the parsing Error stack. Tests exercise every validation branch.
\[search\] Search error:

# Import and RPC negative-path fixtures intentionally submit malformed payloads
# to verify errors are surfaced consistently.
\[import\] (entry rejected|rejected|complete with errors)
\[rpc\] tools/call error
\[registry\] Tool error: (index_search|index_dispatch)
\[HttpTransport\] RPC handler error
\[test\] surface-error

# Admin backup negative-path fixtures intentionally reject empty ZIP uploads
# to verify operator-facing validation without accepting malformed backups.
\[admin\] importZipBackup rejected

# Memory monitor and audit/manifest failure fixtures deliberately exercise
# failure logging paths; these are not operator-actionable in test logs.
\[MemoryMonitor\]
^Memory Status
^Event Listeners:
MEMORY MONITOR REPORT
\[audit\] Failed to persist audit log
\[manifest\] write failed

# Stack traces emitted by deliberate parser/event-buffer negative tests.
Unexpected non-whitespace character after JSON
src[\\/]tests[\\/]eventBuffer\.spec\.ts

# CI runners don't have DirectML/CUDA; embedding service falls back to CPU and warns.
\[embeddingService\] dml provider not available

# Invariant-repair fixture entries (salvage-* / failover-seed-*) are deliberate test
# inputs missing usageCount/firstSeenTs to verify the repair WARN dedup latch.
\[invariant-repair\] (firstSeenTs repair exhausted|usageCount defaulted)
